Below is one way to see how the picture actually breaks down into blocks and how those blocks match the Dictionary images (without re‐orienting them):

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1)  OVERALL ANALYSIS OF THE TARGET IMAGE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
•  The scene has two separate “mini‐structures.”

•  Left Structure (7 blocks total, built in 3 layers plus a top “roof”):
   – Bottom Layer:  
       1 red arch block on the front,  
       1 red rectangular block behind it.  
   – Middle Layer:  
       1 green rectangular block bridging across the two red pieces.  
   – Next Layer:  
       1 yellow rectangular block laid horizontally on top.  
   – Top “Roof/Chimney”:  
       1 orange cylinder in the center (vertical),  
       2 orange wedge blocks (one on each side, forming a roof shape).

•  Right Structure (6 blocks total, built in 2 main horizontal layers with vertical columns):
   – Bottom Yellow Beam:  
       1 horizontal yellow rectangular block.  
   – Two Vertical Green Columns:  
       1 green column on the left,  
       1 green column on the right.  
   – Center Fill (stacked in the middle between the green columns):  
       1 blue cube on the bottom,  
       1 red cube/rectangular block on top of the blue.  
   – Top Yellow Beam:  
       1 additional horizontal yellow rectangular block.

Hence there are 13 total pieces across both structures.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2)  MATCHING DICTIONARY BLOCKS (INDICES)
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is exactly which Dictionary blocks (by index) fit each part—even if repeated.

● LEFT STRUCTURE
   1) Red arch (front, bottom) → Index 2  
   2) Red rectangular block (behind arch) → Index 5  
   3) Green rectangular block (bridging above red blocks) → Index 6  
   4) Yellow rectangular block (next layer) → Index 9  
   5) Orange wedge (left side of “roof”) → Index 15  
   6) Orange wedge (right side of “roof”) → Index 16  
   7) Orange cylinder (center “chimney”) → Index 12  

● RIGHT STRUCTURE
   1) Yellow rectangular block (bottom beam) → Index 9  
   2) Green vertical column (left) → Index 8  
   3) Green vertical column (right) → Index 8  
   4) Blue cube (center lower) → Index 4  
   5) Red block (center above blue) → Index 5  
   6) Yellow rectangular block (top beam) → Index 9  

Note that some indices appear multiple times because the same shape/orientation is used more than once.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
3)  STEP‐BY‐STEP ASSEMBLY ORDER
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Below is a simple bottom‐to‐top build sequence (first building the left structure, then the right).  Use the exact block indices as listed:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 2
  Step2: Move block with index 5
  Step3: Move block with index 6
  Step4: Move block with index 9
  Step5: Move block with index 15
  Step6: Move block with index 16
  Step7: Move block with index 12
  
  Step8: Move block with index 9
  Step9: Move block with index 8
  Step10: Move block with index 8
  Step11: Move block with index 4
  Step12: Move block with index 5
  Step13: Move block with index 9
}

Following these steps will re‐create the two structures exactly as shown in the target image.
